To assess damage to the WM fibers forming the CST, a lesion load (LL) of the affected hemisphere CST was calculated. The overlap volume of the lesion with a probabilistic CST from the Jülich atlas31 was computed according to the wCST-LL method3. The probabilistic CST was linearly transformed into each individual’s native MRI space. For each subject, a weighting factor was obtained from the probability of each voxel in each lesion slice intersecting with the probabilistic CST. Then, the wCST-LL was calculated according to the following equation (1).1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
